data.src_id: Bill Gates, Larry Page, Sergey Brin, Mark Zuckerberg
data.content:

entrepreneurship, technological innovation
These individuals are examples of successful entrepreneurs in technology whose companies pioneered new technologies rather than copying existing models.

Peter Thiel	SpaceX
diversified investment strategy, innovation
The potential strategic connections between PayPal, Facebook investments and SpaceX could suggest his broader interest in technological advancement across different sectors.

Globalization	Technology

While globalization and technology are different modes of progress, they can coexist; they both promote change and development.

Horizontal Progress	Vertical Progress

Horizontal progress involves copying existing solutions whereas vertical progress requires creating something new. Horizontal progress is easier to visualize than vertical progress.
